### Step 1: Setting Up the Node.js Web Application

First, let's create a basic Node.js web application using Express.js. We'll simulate a product and a multi-level marketing scheme.

#### 1.1 Install Node.js and npm

Make sure you have Node.js and npm installed on your system. You can download them from the official Node.js website.

#### 1.2 Create a New Node.js Project

```bash
mkdir mlm-app
cd mlm-app
npm init -y
```

#### 1.3 Install Dependencies

Install Express.js and body-parser for handling HTTP requests and parsing JSON data.

```bash
npm install express body-parser
```

#### 1.4 Create the Web Application

Create a file named `app.js` and add the following code:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');

const app = express();
const PORT = 3000;

app.use(bodyParser.json());

// Simulate a product
const product = {
    name: "UltraGlow Serum",
    price: 50.00,
    description: "A high-quality serum that enhances skin radiance."
};

// Route to get the product details
app.get('/product', (req, res) => {
    res.json(product);
});

// Route to place an order
app.post('/order', (req, res) => {
    const { name, quantity } = req.body;
    const order = {
        name: name,
        quantity: quantity,
        total: product.price * quantity
    };
    res.json(order);
});

app.listen(PORT, () => {
    console.log(`Server is running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});
```

#### 1.5 Run the Web Application

Run the web application using the following command:

```bash
node app.js
```

